Package io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.storage

Class Storage

java.lang.Object
io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.storage.Storage
public class Storage extends Object
Manages temporary storage of test data within a single test execution.

This class provides a thread-safe mechanism for storing, retrieving, and organizing test data using enum keys. Data can be stored at multiple levels, including a hierarchical sub-storage, enabling structured data management during test execution.

The storage supports retrieval of data by key, by index, or by type, and it also supports deferred data creation through the Late interface. Additionally, it offers methods for extracting all matching values based on type.

    • sub

      public Storage sub(Enum<?> subKey)
      Retrieves a sub-storage instance associated with the given sub-key.

      If no sub-storage exists for the given key, a new sub-storage is created and registered.

      Parameters:
      subKey - The enum key for the sub-storage.
      Returns:
      The Storage instance corresponding to the sub-key.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the key is already used for a non-storage value.

    • sub

      public Storage sub()
      Retrieves the default sub-storage.
      Returns:
      The default Storage instance.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if no default storage is initialized.

    • getHookData

      public <T> T getHookData(Object value, Class<T> clazz)
      Retrieves a value stored by a hook (e.g., DbHook or ApiHook) from the global storage map.

      Looks up the HOOKS map under StorageKeysTest.HOOKS and returns the entry associated with the given key object, cast to the specified type.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the type of the returned object
      Parameters:
      value - the hook key under which data was stored
      clazz - the expected class of the stored value
      Returns:
      the hook-stored value cast to T, or null if not present

    • getData

      public Map<Enum<?>,List<Object>> getData()
      Returns a deep copy of all raw storage entries.

      This method creates and returns a new map where each enum key is mapped to a fresh list containing the same elements as the internal storage. Modifications to the returned map or its lists will not affect the original storage.

      Returns:
      a snapshot of the entire storage contents
